PHILLIES SINGLE GAME TICKETS
January 8, 2003

A SPECIAL OFFER FOR ONLINE FANS
We're Starting The Season Early For You! That's right, as a 
valued customer you've been selected to get Early Priority 
Status on Individual Phillies tickets!  

Mark your calendars for Thursday, January 9. Fans ordering
online can make their purchases starting at 6 a.m., a full 
three hours before walkup and phone sales open for business!

With the additions of right-handed pitcher Kevin Millwood, 
first baseman Jim Thome and third baseman David Bell to an 
already talented team, the Phillies will have the hottest 
tickets in town. So don't miss out! Take advantage of your 
Early Priority Status and order online Thursday.

Click below for more info on which games to buy. That way, 
you'll be ready to make your selections.

Phillies Single Game Ticket Information >>
http://lists.mlb.com/u/51570/7327517

If you'd rather purchase in person, we'll be ready with 
coffee and donuts at the Ticket Windows starting at 9 a.m., 
until 5 p.m. Fans should enter the Stadium through the VIP 
entrance on Broad Street. 

For fans who can't get to the Vet or order online, the 
Phillies Phone Center will be taking orders from 9 a.m. 
to 6 p.m. at 215-463-1000. 

In addition, Group Sales will begin January 22 at 9 a.m. 
Season Ticket Sales are ongoing with 2003 season ticket 
holders getting priority seating at the New Ballpark, set 
to open in 2004. This is a great season to make the next 
step up to partial or full season tickets!

Phillies Group Ticket Information >>
http://lists.mlb.com/u/51571/7327517
Phillies Season Ticket Information >>
http://lists.mlb.com/u/51572/7327517

